Filter out --quiet option before passing arguments to GYP

The Freetz-NG build system passes --quiet to configure scripts,
but Node.js's GYP build system doesn't understand this option.
Filter it out from unknown arguments before passing to run_gyp().

--- a/configure.py
+++ b/configure.py
@@ -2176,7 +2176,7 @@ if bin_override is not None:
   gyp_args += ['-Dpython=' + sys.executable]
 
 # pass the leftover non-whitespace positional arguments to GYP
-gyp_args += [arg for arg in args if not str.isspace(arg)]
+gyp_args += [arg for arg in args if not str.isspace(arg) and arg != '--quiet']
 
 if warn.warned and not options.verbose:
   warn('warnings were emitted in the configure phase')